{
  "texts": [
    "4.3.Additional analytical properties of the full model.",
    "We conclude the analysis of our models with a focus on the properties of the whole distribution f (t, A, w).",
    "Even if considering the controlled model and assuming G ≡ 1 and D(w) = √ 1 -w 2, its marginal distributions g(t, A) and h(t, w) converge, the convergence of f (t, A, w) is not guaranteed.",
    "However, if such convergence result holds and f (t, A, w) → t→+∞ f ∞ (A, w), then the marginal distributions of f ∞ (A, w) must be the distributions g ∞ (A) and h ∞ (w) previously introduced.",
    "In particular, in the absence of opinion leaders, we expect f (t, A, w) to converge in the sense of distributions toward the global equilibrium of the Fokker-Planck equation ( 27), given byf ∞ (A, w) = Cδ(A -A * c)(1 -w) -1+ (ωp+ε) 2 νp (1-m in w) (1 + w) -1+ (ωp+ε) 2 νp (1+m in w),where C > 0 is the same normalization constant appearing in (43)."
  ]
}